commands to mount (using udisk)

lsblk will give the device name

> udisksctl mount -b [/dev/DEVICENAME]
> udisksctl unmount -b [/dev/DEVICENAME]

> lsblk -dn | grep -v "nvme0n1 259:0    0  477G  0 disk"
this gives me 
> sda       8:0    1 14.5G  0 disk

> lsblk -o PATH 
this gives me
> PATH
>/dev/sda
>/dev/sda1
>/dev/nvme0n1
>/dev/nvme0n1p1
>/dev/nvme0n1p2
>/dev/nvme0n1p3

> lsblk -e 259 -o KNAME
gives me
> KNAME
> sda
> sda1

> lsblk -e 259 -o PATH -n
/dev/sda
/dev/sda1

> lsblk -e 259 -o KNAME -n | grep -n 1 | tr -d '2:'
=
> sda1
!!!!

